HEADWORD: Rolly-poly
<hw>Roll"y-po`ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of pudding
made of paste spread with fruit, rolled into a cylindrical form, and
boiled or steamed.</def> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Shaped like a
rolly-poly; short and stout.</def></def2> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>roly-poly</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

